{"_id":"1Jg9RzQ24bpHnh7A","name":"Dying","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>Cannot act at all.</p>\n<p>Roll Body vs. 3 as 'death save'; Botch adds Sick, if already Sick add Dead.</p>\n<p>3 successes stabilizes character.</p>\n<p>After combat, roll Body, Speed &amp; Species and see table (at p. 131).</p>\n<p>Others can perform First Aid, rolling Mind &amp; Academics vs. 3, each success grants a bonus d12 to the above roll.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 57.2484%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">Highest dice:&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Result</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">11 or 12</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Replace Dying with Injured, Afraid and Fatigued.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">9 or 10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Replace Dying with Hurt, Injured, Afraid and Fatigued.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">7 or 8</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Replace Dying with Hurt, Injured, Afraid and Sick.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">5 or 6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Replace Dying with Hurt, Injured, Afraid, Confused and Sick.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">3 or 4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Replace Dying with Hurt, Injured, Unconscious and Sick.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Character may make a last-minute speech or dying wish, then become Dead.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 34.747%; text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 64.5428%;\">Character becomes Dead.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by first aid and luck.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"name":"Reeling","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>Retreating causes Knockdown.</p>\n<p>Must Recover on their next turn, otherwise Knocked Down and lose their turn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by Recover or another's Rally.</p>","_id":"2RqmHH9RbzJKjdKA"}
{"name":"Enraged","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Must take an Attack action every round, either at a foe, or simply at inanimate objects.</p>\n<p>If they can Counter, they must Counter.</p>\n<p>Negates Afraid, Asleep, Controlled, Marionette, Paralyzed and Unconscious statuses, is then removed.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by negation or after 5 minutes*.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"2TtNJmDXp79MvLk9"}
{"name":"Half-Buried","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Stride, Dash, Sprint and Run all drop to zero.</p>\n<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>Can claim soft cover (defense d8) from being buried.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed with a Break Free Attack and scoring a success.</p>","_id":"2oqPSchTRfNviHhm"}
{"name":"Hiding","content":"<p>Character has taken a Hide stunt and is hiding behind something that offers at least partial concealment (d8), which is raised to total concealment (d12). Other combatants usually notice the initial Hide stunt but lose track of the character afterwards.</p>\n<p>If the character is hiding behind something that gives cover, its cover rating is also improved by one step: from soft cover (d4), to fair cover (d8), to good cover (d12), to total cover (attack impossible until the cover is destroyed).</p>\n<p>If there is nothing to hide behind, the character may hide by dropping prone. Hiding while prone will allow the character to claim soft cover (d4) and partial concealment (d8) against attacks from further than Near range.</p>\n<p>The character must take the Hide stunt each turn to claim the concealment and cover bonuses, but they are <em>not</em> automatically detected by other combatants when they don't take the stunt.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Removed when the Hide stunt is not taken again.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>(The condition icon could also be used to mark generally out-of-sight or sneaking characters, but in that case, care must be taken not to confuse such characters with ones who have actually taken the Hide stunt.)</em></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.fVjgidNtuEreugmn"}},"_id":"5J32lLlKCtZhFbuR"}
{"_id":"7buKwZrZVy8OwPhx","name":"Hurt","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>+1 Damage received.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by five minutes of first aid, rest, or a common healing spell.</p>"}
{"name":"Silenced","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Cannot be observed with Listen.</p>\n<p>Cannot Rally.</p>\n<p>Cannot use any Magic ability.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed after 5 minutes, or by scoring 3 successes by taking a Recover action and rolling Body, Speed, Mind &amp; Will vs. 5.</p>","_id":"8WNaDcPi0IJbaJAk"}
{"name":"Cannot Move","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pkMTz9xOG6tEK6pm"}},"content":"<p>Character is massively over-encumbered, either by carrying more gear or wearing more layers of armor than they possibly can.</p>\n<p>Cannot move at all.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by not carrying or wearing so much stuff.</p>","_id":"8X3gh1U1g5NQxwbA"}
{"name":"On Fire","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>At the end of their turn, take 2 Damage, worsened by Hurt &amp; Injured.</p>\n<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>Negate concealment from darkness.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed if the fire damage does not cause a new damage result, or is Soaked to zero.</p>\n<p>Rolling on the ground adds Speed to Soak.</p>","_id":"9SQeyWG4sy1vaXO4"}
{"name":"Full Tilt","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>At the start of turn before actions, roll Body and move as many paces in a straight line in the last direction character moved.</p>\n<p>Being unable to move causes Crash.</p>\n<p>Cannot Retreat.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed after aforementioned movement.</p>","_id":"C9275OGG3YcLz1cb"}
{"name":"Confused","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>All targets gain partial concealment (defense bonus d8).</p>\n<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>Must always take a Recover action.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed after 5 minutes*, by another's Rally, or by scoring 2 successes by rolling Mind &amp; Speed vs. 3 at the end of their turn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"E156mwoPTBUaagBB"}
{"name":"Mesmerized","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Cannot consciously remember anything from during Mesmerized.</p>\n<p>Others can influence the character normally.</p>\n<p>The degree of Mesmerized is equal to the successes against the character.</p>\n<p>Each failed influence attempt reduces degrees by one.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Reduced to Confused when degrees hit zero.</p>\n<p>Every 5 minutes, the degrees are reduced by one.</p>","_id":"EMsCXyLEv1SEXIT4"}
{"_id":"HFHtUwuSoZ6wQutn","name":"Sick","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>Reeling causes Knockdown.</p>\n<p>Injured and Fatigued cause the condition to worsen, add 1 to the needed quota.</p>\n<p>New Sick condition makes the character lose all points accrued to the quota.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by time, medical attention and bed rest, by accruing points to a quota. After reaching the quota (usually 24), the Sick condiiton is removed.</p>\n<p>At the end of every cycle (or every second for Twilight), the character rolls Body vs. 3. A botch removes one point, while a success grants one point. Good food, nice bed and a physician can also grant points to the quota.</p>"}
{"name":"Dead","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Character is Dead.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Beyond mortal help.</p>","_id":"JsnatC5y42DGbPP3"}
{"name":"All Fours","permission":{"default":2,"WdFhpciIZfjbRhda":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.S1uHIDeCuhY9C5md"}},"content":"<p>Character is running on all fours, gaining a speed bonus if they have the namesake Gift.</p>\n<p>The character&nbsp;<strong>must</strong> be empty-handed to do this.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed whenever the character wants to.</p>","_id":"MItXHxvNgfSCFenc"}
{"name":"Over-Burdened","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Burdened.</p>\n<p>Can't Run.</p>\n<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by not carrying or wearing so much stuff.</p>","_id":"Ms6nfCALR2RxiwFc"}
{"name":"Fatigued","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Reeling causes Knockdown.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by a short rest.</p>","_id":"O8Cf7H1AoijQfdmL"}
{"name":"Marionette","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Another is controlling the character's actions.</p>\n<p>Controller must use Rally to order Marionettes around.</p>\n<p>Marionette acts right after controller and takes a Recover action, then the ordered action.</p>\n<p>Can speak freely.</p>\n<p>Cannot be ordered to use any Respite, Chapter, Influence or Special Gifts.</p>\n<p>If not given orders, takes Recover and Guard action; in addition:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed when not given orders and scores a success by rolling Mind &amp; Will vs. 3, or after 5 minutes*.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"QJyebhpwRNfvkFEi"}
{"name":"Knockdown","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>Can't Retreat.</p>\n<p>All attacks are Awkward (causing the character to Reel afterwards).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by standing up.</p>","_id":"Rs6XYXEEYOIbUVZo"}
{"_id":"WGljaB1SMqPtXDwC","name":"Focused","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>Can be used to Interrupt others.</p>\n<p>Can be used to take three actions in a turn.</p>\n<p>Mutually negates Reeling.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by using or negation.</p>"}
{"name":"Blinded","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>All targets gain total concealment (defense bonus d12).</p>\n<p>Dash is reduced to zero.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed after 5 minutes*, or by scoring 3 successes by taking a Recover action and rolling Body, Speed &amp; Mind vs. 2.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"XW0PM0eiepT2fqcD"}
{"_id":"XZ1nn0BJoBGtHSYt","name":"Injured","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>+1 Damage received.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by time, medical attention and bed rest, by accruing points to a quota. After reaching the quota (usually 24), the Injured condition is removed.</p>\n<p>Character normally recovers 1 point per day. Good food, nice bed and a physician can speed the recovery.</p>\n<p>Cannot be removed if Sick.</p>"}
{"_id":"ZzpRbp4XIFV5y8rW","name":"Guarding","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>Dodges, Parries and Counter-Attacks can claim a bonus d8 (d12 with Veteran).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed at the start of their next turn.</p>"}
{"name":"Berserk","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Must take an Attack action every round at the nearest combatant, friend or foe, or at inanimate objects if nothing else.</p>\n<p>If they can Counter, they must Counter.</p>\n<p>Negates Afraid, Asleep, Controlled, Marionette, Paralyzed and Unconscious statuses, is then removed.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by negation, after lacking a target for 12 rounds.</p>\n<p>Reduced to Enraged by scoring one success when they defeat a foe and roll Mind &amp; Will.</p>","_id":"dtpk97W1sWJY68zF"}
{"name":"Asleep","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Helpless and potentially out of the fight.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by loud noises within 100 paces, being sent Reeling, or by another's Rally.</p>","_id":"fy5EtGmfIZbpbqd1"}
{"name":"Overkilled","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Character is Very Dead.</p>\n<p>Allies within Near (4 paces) become Afraid.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Even further beyond mortal help.</p>","_id":"iL6ssGkLXwHPqRLh"}
{"name":"Afraid","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Cannot Attack, Rally, or take a Focus round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by another's Rally or by being out of sight of all enemies.</p>","_id":"krkg0YwKTNyD8BPM"}
{"name":"Grappled","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.oDHml7d5J5hxg0B5"}},"content":"<p>Grappled target cannot move away from attacker. Target can only keep the same distance or decrease the distance to the attacker. They cannot Retreat from their attacker.</p>\n<p>Attacker cannot use the weapon used for Grappled for anything else while grappling.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed when the attacker releases the target (a free reaction), Retreats for <em>any</em> reason, or is incapacitated. Also removed if the target successfully escapes (commonly Break Free).</p>","_id":"lQRKvbZYOo7izSdT"}
{"name":"Immobilized","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Stride, Dash, Sprint and Run all drop to zero.</p>\n<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed after 5 minutes*.</p>\n<p>Reduced to Slowed by scoring 2 successes by rolling Speed &amp; Will vs. 3 at the end of their turn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"lveZKbwsOHC8wg25"}
{"_id":"nbQkEI0uPTHdQtPk","name":"Slowed","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>Disadvantaged: Others claim a bonus d8 to hit, can't Counter.</p>\n<p>Stride and Dash drop to zero: can't Retreat due to zero Stride.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed after 5 minutes*, or by scoring 2 successes by rolling Speed &amp; Will vs. 3 at the end of their turn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>"}
{"name":"Burdened","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Dash is zero.</p>\n<p>Limit of d8 to Speed Dice and ⛝ Skills.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by not carrying or wearing so much stuff.</p>","_id":"pJTP7nRDfLCXTAzO"}
{"name":"Controlled","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Another is controlling the character's mind.</p>\n<p>Controller must use Rally to control a target, rolling vs. standard difficulty.</p>\n<p>Character switches sides and acts right after controller, taking the Recover action, then ordered action, and is then sent Reeling.</p>\n<p>If not Rallied, the character takes the Recover and Guard actions.</p>\n<p>Character can Parry or Dodge, and will only Counter if they choose so.</p>\n<p>Character believes everything done while Controlled are their own ideas, being Rallied by another can break this.</p>\n<p>Character can speak freely.</p>\n<p>Character cannot be ordered to use any Respite, Chapter or Special Gifts.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed with Mesmerism*.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"rjHftAZgQQTg41ag"}
{"name":"Terrified","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Cannot Attack, Rally, or take a Focus round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by being Reasoned with, or by keeping the source of fear out of sight for 5 minutes*.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"soFkqUQFGaY3Q8IM"}
{"name":"Unconscious","permission":{"default":2,"XGpjZ2avIKpWZLRi":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Helpless and out of the fight.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed by another's Rally or with one hour of sleep*.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>*= May vary depending on source.</p>","_id":"y17nrzjqcBNdnyVo"}
{"name":"Flying","permission":{"default":2,"WdFhpciIZfjbRhda":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pwj7pSbHXjhFxyOG"}},"content":"<p>The character is currently flying on their own power. They must take the \"fly\" action on every turn as well as \"refresh\" the Gift of Flight that lets them fly on every turn.</p>\n<p>Please refer to the full rules in the core book, at pages 66-68.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Removed when the \"fly\" action is not taken, preferably while landed. Otherwise, falling damage rules come into effect.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"zghrfBq4iiKosTKu"}
